Feel free to give them assignments too.

112
00:07:23,401 --> 00:07:24,819
Yes, of course.

113
00:07:30,450 --> 00:07:31,493
Come in.

114
00:07:32,577 --> 00:07:35,204
Sir, the defendant
for the court-appointed case is here.

115
00:07:35,205 --> 00:07:37,165
Okay. Is she in the conference room?

116
00:07:41,419 --> 00:07:42,921
INDICTMENT
DEFENDANT DO MIKYUNG

117
00:07:48,635 --> 00:07:51,220
NEW LOAN OFFER
EMERGENCY LOANS FOR LOW CREDIT SCORES

118
00:07:51,221 --> 00:07:53,514
I'm sorry. Things are tough right now,

119
00:07:53,515 --> 00:07:55,641
so I could only use
a court-appointed lawyer.

120
00:07:55,642 --> 00:07:58,561
Not at all. Don't worry about that.

121
00:07:59,396 --> 00:08:02,356
You've been charged
with aiding and abetting fraud.

122
00:08:02,357 --> 00:08:04,526
You know why you've been charged, right?

123
00:08:05,110 --> 00:08:07,736
Charged? What does that exactly mean?

124
00:08:07,737 --> 00:08:10,989
Even if I read it,
I honestly have no idea what it means.

125
00:08:10,990 --> 00:08:14,827
So the prosecution believes
you committed a crime,

126
00:08:14,828 --> 00:08:16,537
so they've sent this case to trial.

127
00:08:16,538 --> 00:08:18,414
That's what we call being "charged."

128
00:08:18,415 --> 00:08:20,541
They're charges
of aiding and abetting fraud.

129
00:08:20,542 --> 00:08:22,710
I get the fraud part,

130
00:08:22,711 --> 00:08:24,712
but what does "aiding and abetting" mean?

131
00:08:24,713 --> 00:08:27,172
Does it mean
I just stood by while it happened?

132
00:08:27,173 --> 00:08:29,299
That's a common misunderstanding.

133
00:08:29,300 --> 00:08:32,177
It means you helped, not just stood by.

134
00:08:32,178 --> 00:08:34,138
It's a type of accomplice.

135
00:08:34,139 --> 00:08:36,224
You're saying I helped commit fraud?

136
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:41,228
Yes, it says you were involved
in a voice phishing scheme.

137
00:08:41,229 --> 00:08:43,398
You acted as a money mule.

138
00:08:44,774 --> 00:08:49,820
They're saying you withdrew the money
from the scam and handed it off.

139
00:08:49,821 --> 00:08:53,366
That's not true.
All I did was just try to get a loan.

140
00:08:56,494 --> 00:08:58,203
According to the indictment,

141
00:08:58,204 --> 00:09:02,082
after getting a text from someone
calling himself Baek from BX Bank,

142
00:09:02,083 --> 00:09:03,792
you spoke with him on the phone.

143
00:09:03,793 --> 00:09:05,544
Do you remember what was said?

144
00:09:05,545 --> 00:09:08,881
Yes. At first, he said
I wouldn't qualify for a loan.

145
00:09:08,882 --> 00:09:10,758
But then, he said he'd make sure

146
00:09:10,759 --> 00:09:12,259
to help me out to get a loan.

147
00:09:12,260 --> 00:09:15,929
<i>Your account hasn't had much activity,
so your credit rating is low.</i>

148
00:09:15,930 --> 00:09:18,183
<i>We'll help you create
some transactions first.</i>

149
00:09:19,184 --> 00:09:20,393
In my bank account?

150
00:09:22,645 --> 00:09:24,980
<i>I'm only suggesting this
since I trust you, Ms. Do.</i>

151
00:09:24,981 --> 00:09:26,107
Here you go.

152
00:09:30,320 --> 00:09:32,571
<i>First, I'll deposit some money
into your account</i>

153
00:09:32,572 --> 00:09:34,114
<i>to create some transactions.</i>

154
00:09:34,115 --> 00:09:35,991
Thank you.

155
00:09:35,992 --> 00:09:39,954
<i>But you can't keep that money.
You have to return it to us.</i>

156
00:09:43,124 --> 00:09:45,794
- Great job, ma'am.
- Thank you.

157
00:09:46,878 --> 00:09:48,379
Thank you.

158
00:09:51,758 --> 00:09:54,928
But in the end,
he never gave me the loan.

159
00:09:58,223 --> 00:10:00,600
Do you happen
to have a recording of that phone call?

160
00:10:01,184 --> 00:10:02,559
I'm not sure.

161
00:10:02,560 --> 00:10:05,355
- Could I see your phone again?
- Of course.

162
00:10:08,608 --> 00:10:11,027
This happened last November, so...

163
00:10:13,780 --> 00:10:14,864
Here it is.

164
00:10:15,824 --> 00:10:16,824
Here.

165
00:10:16,825 --> 00:10:18,284
BX BANK
BAEK JEONGHYEON

166
00:10:19,577 --> 00:10:22,538
<i>Hello, this is Baek Jeonghyeon
with BX Bank. How may I help you?</i>

167
00:10:22,539 --> 00:10:26,209
<i>I'm calling about the text I got.</i>

168
00:10:26,793 --> 00:10:27,960
The call was recorded.

169
00:10:27,961 --> 00:10:30,380
- Were you questioned by the police alone?
- Yes.

170
00:10:30,964 --> 00:10:34,509
It seems what you just said
wasn't conveyed, so they charged you.

171
00:10:35,385 --> 00:10:37,094
If this recording had been submitted,

172
00:10:37,095 --> 00:10:40,681
it would've been clear
that you were tricked and not involved.

173
00:10:40,682 --> 00:10:43,392
Am I okay then?

174
00:10:43,393 --> 00:10:45,477
It wasn't voice phishing, right?

175
00:10:45,478 --> 00:10:47,230
Well...

176
00:10:47,981 --> 00:10:52,234
The voice phishing victims did transfer
money into your account though.

177
00:10:52,235 --> 00:10:56,990
And you did withdraw that money
and handed it over to the scammers.

178
00:10:58,116 --> 00:10:59,867
But you didn't know it was a scam.

179
00:10:59,868 --> 00:11:01,369
I had no idea.

180
00:11:01,953 --> 00:11:05,414
I also wondered if this was
some kind of voice phishing

181
00:11:05,415 --> 00:11:06,748
and asked him about it.

182
00:11:06,749 --> 00:11:08,501
But he told me it wasn't that.

183
00:11:09,043 --> 00:11:11,753
He didn't ask me for money or anything.

184
00:11:11,754 --> 00:11:15,341
He just said he'd give me a loan,
so I believed him.

185
00:11:15,925 --> 00:11:17,634
Don't worry too much about it.

186
00:11:17,635 --> 00:11:20,305
If you submit
a transcript of this recording,

187
00:11:20,889 --> 00:11:22,140
it'll prove your innocence.

188
00:11:22,724 --> 00:11:26,227
Goodness. Thank you, Attorney Cho!

189
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,355
INDICTMENT
DEFENDANT DO MIKYUNG

190
00:11:30,648 --> 00:11:33,734
<i>The main voice phishing scammers
are usually overseas,</i>

191
00:11:33,735 --> 00:11:37,112
so I heard they track down
all the money mules here

192
00:11:37,113 --> 00:11:38,697
and push for heavy sentences.

193
00:11:38,698 --> 00:11:40,824
I heard some get a few years in prison.

194
00:11:40,825 --> 00:11:44,620
Still, she didn't even know
she was used as a money mule.

195
00:11:44,621 --> 00:11:47,373
How can they charge her
after such a sloppy investigation?

196
00:11:51,836 --> 00:11:53,337
Still can't get a hold of him?

197
00:11:53,338 --> 00:11:55,297
No. It's so annoying.

198
00:11:55,298 --> 00:11:58,300
If I ever get my hands on this bastard...

199
00:11:58,301 --> 00:12:00,219
That unpaid construction cost son of a...

200
00:12:00,220 --> 00:12:01,888
- That person?
- Yeah.

201
00:12:02,639 --> 00:12:05,641
We have a site inspection tomorrow.
What is he doing?

202
00:12:05,642 --> 00:12:07,768
I asked for documents,
but I can't reach him.

203
00:12:07,769 --> 00:12:09,228
Filing isn't the end, okay?

204
00:12:09,229 --> 00:12:10,562
Calm down.

205
00:12:10,563 --> 00:12:12,356
The building's not even finished.

206
00:12:12,357 --> 00:12:15,275
They stopped over a payment issue,

207
00:12:15,276 --> 00:12:18,403
so someone who knows the details
needs to be there.

208
00:12:18,404 --> 00:12:21,282
The client's all carefree,
and I'm the one who's stressed.

209
00:12:22,075 --> 00:12:24,326
You'd think I was the one being stiffed.

210
00:12:24,327 --> 00:12:25,954
I did think that.

211
00:12:28,790 --> 00:12:31,291
Hey, it's nice being at a cafe though.

212
00:12:31,292 --> 00:12:33,586
We've always been stuck
in the break room lately.

213
00:12:34,170 --> 00:12:36,797
Are those interns set up
in the break room?

214
00:12:36,798 --> 00:12:38,757
Yeah, did they stop by and say hi?

215
00:12:38,758 --> 00:12:40,759
They asked us to drop by now and then.

216
00:12:40,760 --> 00:12:43,137
- Yeah, they did.
- Was I that baby-faced back then?

217
00:12:43,721 --> 00:12:44,722
They were cute.

218
00:12:46,015 --> 00:12:47,517
They didn't come say hi to me.

219
00:12:48,101 --> 00:12:49,102
Hey.

220
00:12:50,144 --> 00:12:52,689
I guess Ms. Kim also knows now
that you're a jerk.

221
00:12:53,356 --> 00:12:54,731
What are you going to do now?

222
00:12:54,732 --> 00:12:57,401
I was out this morning.
They must've come by then.

223
00:12:57,402 --> 00:13:00,862
Shouldn't we at least do a welcome dinner
or something for them tonight?

224
00:13:00,863 --> 00:13:01,948
I can't tonight.

225
00:13:02,490 --> 00:13:05,409
The contractor probably
won't even show tomorrow,

226
00:13:05,410 --> 00:13:08,620
so I'll have to comb through
whatever documents I have.

227
00:13:08,621 --> 00:13:09,706
How about tomorrow?

228
00:13:10,331 --> 00:13:11,332
I have plans.

229
00:13:11,874 --> 00:13:14,209
- With who?
- He's meeting his high school friends.

230
00:13:14,210 --> 00:13:18,881
Even though I'm in early pregnancy,
my husband insisted on going too.

231
00:13:20,258 --> 00:13:23,635
He said you hadn't come in a while
and used you as his excuse.

232
00:13:23,636 --> 00:13:26,138
He said I needed to be there
as his excuse.

233
00:13:26,139 --> 00:13:27,723
He's buying
to celebrate the baby.

234
00:13:27,724 --> 00:13:30,600
Ridiculous.
Does he think he's the pregnant one?

235
00:13:30,601 --> 00:13:33,854
I can just make plans for tomorrow too.
Let's have the dinner then.

236
00:13:33,855 --> 00:13:35,230
- Sure.
- Yeah, do it tomorrow.

237
00:13:35,231 --> 00:13:37,107
Ms. Kim didn't ask Juhyeong,

238
00:13:37,108 --> 00:13:38,735
- so he won't have to come.
- Right?

239
00:13:39,319 --> 00:13:40,653
I told you I was out then.

240
00:13:55,334 --> 00:13:56,377
Yes.

241
00:14:05,803 --> 00:14:07,846
- Hello!
- Hello!

242
00:14:07,847 --> 00:14:10,390
There's no need to be so formal with us.

243
00:14:10,391 --> 00:14:12,726
Have a seat.
I'm not a professor or your boss.

244
00:14:12,727 --> 00:14:14,186
- Please sit.
- Okay.

245
00:14:14,187 --> 00:14:15,605
- Thank you.
- You're sitting?

246
00:14:17,106 --> 00:14:19,274
I'm just kidding! Sit down.

247
00:14:19,275 --> 00:14:20,359
Okay.

248
00:14:24,322 --> 00:14:25,363
UNJUST ENRICHMENT

249
00:14:25,364 --> 00:14:27,657
- Have you read this too?
- No, not yet.

