<i>When should we go to your aunt's tomorrow?</i>

1017
01:02:39,839 --> 01:02:43,635
I think I need
to stop by the office tomorrow.

1018
01:02:44,970 --> 01:02:45,971
<i>Are you that busy?</i>

1019
01:02:46,721 --> 01:02:49,224
I just have a bunch
of little things to take care of.

1020
01:02:50,433 --> 01:02:52,310
Okay. Bye.

1021
01:02:59,943 --> 01:03:01,068
What are you doing here?

1022
01:03:01,069 --> 01:03:03,488
I thought you'd be glued
to your parents all break.

1023
01:03:04,072 --> 01:03:05,865
There's not much to do at home.

1024
01:03:06,491 --> 01:03:08,409
I guess I'm a full-fledged lawyer now.

1025
01:03:08,410 --> 01:03:10,704
The office just feels more peaceful.

1026
01:03:12,122 --> 01:03:13,163
How about you?

1027
01:03:13,164 --> 01:03:16,710
Well, I've been a lawyer for a long time.

1028
01:03:27,846 --> 01:03:28,888
Do you...

1029
01:03:29,973 --> 01:03:30,974
want to grab a bite?

1030
01:03:32,767 --> 01:03:33,768
Sure.

1031
01:03:36,604 --> 01:03:37,605
This way?

1032
01:03:38,690 --> 01:03:39,691
Here?

1033
01:03:41,776 --> 01:03:44,029
Don't you smell something delicious?

1034
01:03:44,988 --> 01:03:46,990
I've been frying <i>jeon</i> all day.

1035
01:03:47,657 --> 01:03:49,199
Doesn't your family make <i>jeon?</i>

1036
01:03:49,200 --> 01:03:50,785
We make dumplings.

1037
01:03:51,286 --> 01:03:53,288
- Dumplings?
- Don't you smell dumplings?

1038
01:03:55,331 --> 01:03:57,459
How would clothes
ever smell like dumplings?

1039
01:03:58,251 --> 01:04:02,839
- You know, like from dumpling hot pot.
- I see. So you had dumpling hot pot?

1040
01:04:03,631 --> 01:04:05,050
We had hot pot and...

1041
01:04:08,762 --> 01:04:11,765
Gosh, even this place is empty now.

1042
01:04:12,348 --> 01:04:14,309
Right? Every place is closed.

1043
01:04:15,101 --> 01:04:17,020
Maybe places
near Gangnam Station are open?

1044
01:04:18,104 --> 01:04:19,689
Wow, Gangnam Station.

1045
01:04:21,316 --> 01:04:23,902
I know a place there
that's open for 24 hours.

1046
01:04:25,028 --> 01:04:26,987
On the night you stood me up,

1047
01:04:26,988 --> 01:04:29,699
I was so cold
I ended up eating there alone.

1048
01:04:30,241 --> 01:04:33,036
It's still around,
and I get angry every time I pass by.

1049
01:04:36,456 --> 01:04:37,916
No wonder I couldn't find you.

1050
01:04:39,084 --> 01:04:40,085
What?

1051
01:04:41,878 --> 01:04:42,879
Well...

1052
01:04:44,089 --> 01:04:45,507
I went to Gangnam Station too.

1053
01:04:46,508 --> 01:04:47,509
You're lying.

1054
01:04:49,260 --> 01:04:51,553
I'm not like you. Why would I lie?

1055
01:04:51,554 --> 01:04:53,055
Why are you saying this now?

1056
01:04:53,056 --> 01:04:56,351
Well, I missed the right moment to say it.

1057
01:05:02,190 --> 01:05:03,441
I still can't believe it.

1058
01:05:05,193 --> 01:05:08,195
How could you possibly take that
as me canceling?

1059
01:05:08,196 --> 01:05:10,572
No, we definitely agreed to meet,

1060
01:05:10,573 --> 01:05:12,783
but then, you asked if we'd be together.

1061
01:05:12,784 --> 01:05:15,537
In my mind, I was basically
confessing my feelings for you.

1062
01:05:16,371 --> 01:05:18,247
We were running out of time together.

1063
01:05:18,248 --> 01:05:22,168
You even said we should meet in Seoul,
but you still didn't ask me out.

1064
01:05:26,965 --> 01:05:30,260
Next time, whatever it is,
say it clearly so I can understand.

1065
01:05:33,304 --> 01:05:34,514
Next time when?

1066
01:05:50,238 --> 01:05:51,406
Now?

1067
01:06:09,757 --> 01:06:11,259
Is that clear enough?

1068
01:06:16,472 --> 01:06:17,849
Do you think I'm an idiot?

1069
01:07:03,770 --> 01:07:05,438
So, what do you want to eat?

1070
01:07:10,568 --> 01:07:11,652
Acai bowl.

1071
01:07:11,653 --> 01:07:12,778
Acai bowl?

1072
01:07:12,779 --> 01:07:14,447
- What's this?
- What on earth?

1073
01:07:18,660 --> 01:07:19,661
What?

1074
01:07:20,245 --> 01:07:22,246
- What are you doing here?
- What's going on?

1075
01:07:22,247 --> 01:07:25,374
- Did you make plans without me?
- Don't be ridiculous.

1076
01:07:25,375 --> 01:07:26,917
Why are you here?

1077
01:07:26,918 --> 01:07:28,877
- Where's your husband?
- He's asleep.

1078
01:07:28,878 --> 01:07:30,587
Hold on.

1079
01:07:30,588 --> 01:07:32,798
Then, did we run into each other
by chance?

1080
01:07:32,799 --> 01:07:34,716
Why is he so excited?

1081
01:07:34,717 --> 01:07:36,427
It's exciting! It feels like fate!

1082
01:07:37,178 --> 01:07:38,679
- Geez.
- Geez.

1083
01:07:38,680 --> 01:07:40,014
Perfect. It's snowing too.

1084
01:07:41,975 --> 01:07:44,102
I can't believe nothing was open.

1085
01:07:44,811 --> 01:07:46,937
You said it was open 24 hours.

1086
01:07:46,938 --> 01:07:48,939
I never said 365 days a year.

1087
01:07:48,940 --> 01:07:50,024
Geez.

1088
01:07:56,572 --> 01:07:58,741
Hey, what are you all doing?

1089
01:07:59,534 --> 01:08:00,534
What?

1090
01:08:00,535 --> 01:08:01,702
What's up with you two?

1091
01:08:01,703 --> 01:08:03,328
Did you make plans without us?

1092
01:08:03,329 --> 01:08:07,417
No, I was here first.
And then, Juhyeong showed up too.

1093
01:08:08,584 --> 01:08:11,796
Well, I was on my way to the office,
and she was standing outside.

1094
01:08:13,423 --> 01:08:15,090
- What does that mean?
- Suspicious.

1095
01:08:15,091 --> 01:08:16,300
Whatever. Just eat.

1096
01:08:16,301 --> 01:08:18,343
- I want that one.
- Yeah.

1097
01:08:18,344 --> 01:08:21,847
I was worried two pies would be too much,
but it worked out. Let's eat.

1098
01:08:21,848 --> 01:08:24,057
Hey, aren't you curious
why we're all here?

1099
01:08:24,058 --> 01:08:25,226
It's obvious.

1100
01:08:26,561 --> 01:08:28,104
I didn't take a picture. Hold on.

1101
01:08:28,688 --> 01:08:30,648
I took one earlier. I'll send it to you.

1102
01:08:31,316 --> 01:08:33,067
I have my own artistic style though.

1103
01:08:33,860 --> 01:08:36,529
- I took a good one.
- Thanks.

1104
01:08:45,621 --> 01:08:47,622
It's nice to be in the break room again.

1105
01:08:47,623 --> 01:08:48,833
You're right.

1106
01:08:49,834 --> 01:08:51,586
This place feels the most comfortable.

1107
01:08:59,177 --> 01:09:00,970
It's really snowing a lot.

1108
01:09:53,981 --> 01:09:55,024
Hi, Mom.

1109
01:09:57,026 --> 01:09:58,027
What?

1110
01:11:19,358 --> 01:11:22,528
Law and The City

1111
01:11:50,890 --> 01:11:54,601
Law and The City

1112
01:11:54,602 --> 01:11:56,436
<i>You should've told me about this!</i>

1113
01:11:56,437 --> 01:11:59,689
What do you mean there's nothing?
You got it through Park!

1114
01:11:59,690 --> 01:12:01,566
- It couldn't be...
<i>- Her father...</i>

1115
01:12:01,567 --> 01:12:02,944
<i>was in jail.</i>

1116
01:12:04,195 --> 01:12:05,529
Are you okay?

1117
01:12:05,530 --> 01:12:07,406
You're going through a lot.

1118
01:12:08,866 --> 01:12:10,450
You're not defending this, right?

1119
01:12:10,451 --> 01:12:11,910
Dad.

1120
01:12:11,911 --> 01:12:14,455
Don't come back anymore. Okay?

1121
01:12:17,250 --> 01:12:19,418
Wait, you think this contract is legit?

1122
01:12:20,753 --> 01:12:23,256
It's Huiji's father.
Aren't you being too impersonal?

1123
01:12:24,215 --> 01:12:25,799
<i>I'm visiting as his attorney.</i>

1124
01:12:25,800 --> 01:12:28,344
<i>Please tell him to come out. Please.</i>

1125
01:12:36,269 --> 01:12:38,271
Translated by Hye Min Eom
